    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan I've researched and designed:\n\n---\n\n## What I'll build\n\n**2 new files + 2 registry edits.** No existing files are touched except to add entries.\n\n### `stepper.tsx` — Architecture\n\nModeled directly after `carousel.tsx` (the best context-based compound component in the codebase). Uses **two React contexts**:\n\n| Context | Provider | Shared Values |\n|---|---|---|\n| `StepperContext` | `Stepper` root | `activeStep`, `orientation` |\n| `StepperItemContext` | Each `StepperItem` | `step`, computed `state` |\n\nState is computed in `StepperItem`: `step < activeStep` → `\"completed\"`, `step === activeStep` → `\"active\"`, `step > activeStep` → `\"pending\"`.\n\n### 7 exports\n\n`Stepper`, `StepperItem`, `StepperTrigger`, `StepperTitle`, `StepperDescription`, `StepperSeparator`, `StepperContent` + `stepperTriggerVariants`\n\n### Key design decision: `StepperSeparator` inside `StepperItem`\n\nThe separator must live **inside** `<StepperItem>` to access `StepperItemContext` for its visual state. When `state === \"completed\"`, it fills with `bg-primary` — matching the requirement that it updates when the next step becomes active.\n\n### `stepperTriggerVariants` (CVA)\n\nThree state variants: `active` + `completed` → filled primary circle; `pending` → bordered muted circle.\n\n### Registry entries\n\n- UI: `dependencies: [\"class-variance-authority\"]` (needs `cva`; no Radix UI)\n- Example: `registryDependencies: [\"stepper\", \"button\"]` (demo uses both)\n- UI entry goes between `spinner` and `switch` (alphabetically, line ~563)\n- Example entry appends at end of file (line 2651)",
